A vintage 1950s-style illustration of two mechanical mail sorting machines facing each other across a conveyor belt, one sleek and blue, the other bulky and amber-colored. Between them, colorful paper task cards with checkboxes float through pneumatic tubes that twist and intertwine like ribbons. The machines have analog dials, spinning gears, and small robotic arms attempting to catch and process the flying cards. The background features a retro office environment with warm wood paneling and frosted glass windows. The color palette emphasizes warm oranges, cool blues, and cream tones, with subtle halftone dot patterns typical of mid-century print advertisements.
